101
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:10,080
Exactly.

102
00:06:15,880 --> 00:06:17,080
They've already left.

103
00:06:18,360 --> 00:06:19,360
Good.

104
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:21,800
I did as you said.

105
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:23,360
What should I do

106
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:24,800
to let you release my parents?

107
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:26,480
Since I'm here,

108
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:29,160
I'll let your family stay together.

109
00:06:29,920 --> 00:06:31,000
When night falls,

110
00:06:31,320 --> 00:06:32,640
I'll let it happen.

111
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:36,800
Stop.

112
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:39,600
A Cha, I'm late.

113
00:06:39,640 --> 00:06:40,560
Are you hurt?

114
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:01,960
Are you really the best assassin
in White Tiger?

115
00:07:11,720 --> 00:07:12,760
You disappointed me

116
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:14,200
but charged me so much.

117
00:07:16,440 --> 00:07:18,000
Where did you find the assassin?

118
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:21,040
Info from the black market.

119
00:07:24,520 --> 00:07:25,160
Here.

120
00:07:31,040 --> 00:07:34,880
Assassin services, guaranteed quality
with first-class skills.

121
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:36,440
899, one-on-one.

122
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:38,400
999, one-to-many.

123
00:07:38,680 --> 00:07:40,960
Numerous assassins,
full range of services.

124
00:07:44,320 --> 00:07:46,560
One client at a time.
No refund if assassination fails.

125
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:49,600
If you want a refund,
please come to the Cheat Mountain

126
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:51,880
in Azure Dragon on the thirtieth day
of the second month.

127
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:00,520
Cheat Mountain?

128
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:02,680
I was fooled?

129
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:05,280
The characters are too small to be seen.

130
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:09,520
So what should we do now?

131
00:08:11,080 --> 00:08:12,960
Let that kitchen maid come back
to the palace?

132
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:16,120
If something is discovered, then...

133
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:19,720
Since she wants to investigate it,

134
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:22,440
why don't we help her?

135
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:23,960
Help her?

136
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:30,480
I'm sorry.

137
00:08:30,960 --> 00:08:32,160
It was all my fault.

138
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:34,960
I shouldn't have been self-righteous

139
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:36,520
and acted on my own.

140
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:39,080
I shouldn't have said harsh words
and thought

141
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:40,680
it was for your good.

142
00:08:40,680 --> 00:08:43,080
I shouldn't have pushed you away
and made you sad.

143
00:08:46,640 --> 00:08:48,400
We don't belong in the same world.

144
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:49,840
Why do you say that

145
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:51,920
to a kitchen maid like me?

146
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:54,160
Can you forget what I said before?

147
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:56,160
That's not what I meant.

148
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:57,080
No.

149
00:08:57,160 --> 00:08:58,760
I don't have many other merits,

150
00:08:58,760 --> 00:08:59,960
except for a good memory.

151
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:04,840
A Cha, when you weren't in the palace,

152
00:09:05,560 --> 00:09:06,800
I was restless.

153
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:11,360
When I closed my eyes,
all I saw was you in my head.

154
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:13,080
I don't want to lose you.

155
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:15,480
Can you forgive me?

156
00:09:16,560 --> 00:09:18,040
I don't want to forgive you.

157
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:20,480
What do I have to do
for you to forgive me?

158
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:22,554
♪For you, I'd be the last pedal♪

159
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:24,720
You promise me one thing.

160
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:25,960
No problem.

161
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:28,360
I can even promise you a million things.

162
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:30,680
As long as you say it, I'll do it.

163
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:32,240
Keep your word.

164
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:35,960
Starting today,

165
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:37,440
you have to be obedient to me.

166
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:39,240
You have to pamper me
and don't deceive me.

167
00:09:39,280 --> 00:09:40,840
And you can't leave me.

168
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:43,320
You can't lose your temper at me

169
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:44,800
or scold me.

170
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:47,280
When I am happy,
you should be happy too.

171
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:48,240
When I am not happy,

172
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:49,440
you should cheer me up.

173
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:51,080
Stay with me and think of me.

174
00:09:51,080 --> 00:09:52,080
There are 24 hours a day,

175
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:54,000
but you have to think of me
for 25 hours a day.

176
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:54,720
Can you promise?

177
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:56,040
Yes.

178
00:09:57,760 --> 00:10:00,000
Starting today,

179
00:10:00,280 --> 00:10:02,240
forget that stupid curse.

180
00:10:02,680 --> 00:10:03,880
You're not a jinx.

181
00:10:04,440 --> 00:10:06,120
Back then, you were just a child.

182
00:10:06,560 --> 00:10:08,200
You did nothing wrong.

183
00:10:08,680 --> 00:10:10,960
You've just been
in that cage for too long.

184
00:10:14,688 --> 00:10:17,440
♪Tears in solitude,
how often they start♪

185
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:18,520
With you by my side,

186
00:10:19,680 --> 00:10:20,640
I can pull through.

187
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:24,760
We should cherish the present.

188
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:27,120
For our present and future,

189
00:10:27,920 --> 00:10:29,400
